<div id="mission">
    <p>
        The famous saying by Mahatma Gandhi, “When you educate a girl, you educate a community”
        has been proven again, by the works of Pardada Pardadi School, (PPES). The entire
        village of Anoopshahar in Bulandshahr Distict of UP has been amazingly transposed
        in just a few years. At PPES access to free education alone was insufficient to
        keep girls in school, the plan included 10 Rupees (equivalent to $0.30 US) per attendance,
        per girl to be deposited into their personal bank accounts. The learning and earning
        scheme developed by Mr. Singh, the founder of the school, was put into action. In
        the morning, girls attend academic classes, such as Math, Science, English, Social
        Studies, and Creative Arts. In the afternoon, the girls are trained in manufacturing
        handy crafts and textiles. By the time the students graduate, they not only have
        basic academic skills but also develop highly marketable vocational job skills.
        As an added bonus, at graduation they would get approximately $700 us to jump start
        their lives. What an inspiration to see the impact and amazing power of education
        in the lives of these girls and their families.
    </p>
